@NODE "datasheet" "fuelgauge_gc/datasheet (information)"


    NAME
        @{"fuelgauge_gc" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/fuelgauge_gc/MAIN"} -- create fuelgauge BOOPSI objects

    SUPERCLASS
        gadgetclass

    REQUIRES
        bevel.image

    DESCRIPTION
        The fuelgauge gadget class is used to display stage of completion
        of some operation, such as formating a floppy. Or, perhaps as
        a means of indication, such as free drive space.

        Advantages that this class provides:

         > Supports window relativity.

         > Optional tick marks, and short ticks.

         > Ability to change background pen, text pen, and filltext pen.

         > Supports OS 3.0 BOOPSI Gadget HelpTest.

    METHODS
        @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} -- Passed to superclass to creates object instance

        @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} -- Sets all possible settings, then passed to superclass

        @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66} -- Returns requested setting or passed to superclass

        @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64} -- Passed to superclass

        @{"GM_HITTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 298} -- Returns 0.

        @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302} -- Passed to superclass, then renders fuelgauge

        @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323} -- Returns @{"GDOMAIN_MINIMUM" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 486}, @{"GDOMAIN_NOMINAL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 489} and
            @{"GDOMAIN_MAXIMUM" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 492} dimensions.

        @{"GM_GOACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 305} -- NO OP
        @{"GM_HANDLEINPUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 308} -- NO OP
        @{"GM_GOINACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 311} -- NO OP

    ATTRIBUTES

        @{"GA_Text" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 62} (@{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67})
            Used to specify the @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} terminated string to use
            as the text for the gadget.  The @{"Text()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/Text"} function is used to draw
            the text. @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} is valid input, and will enable the default
            centered percentage rendering. Changing the label will invoke
            @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302}. Text string is clipped to fit inside the gauge via
            the @{"TextFit()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/graphics/TextFit"} function. The text string may contain varargs
            format specifiers compatible to @{"RawDoFmt()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/exec/RawDoFmt"} if the varargs data
            is supplied via @{"FUELGAUGE_VarArgs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 63}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Min" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 27} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Minimum value of the gauge.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Max" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 30} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Maximum value of the gauge.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Level" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 33} (@{"LONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 51})
            Current gauge setting, usually something between Min and Max.
            Base on Min, Max and Current a percentage can be calculated
            and displayed by the gadget.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Orientation" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 36} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Sets the orientation of the fuel gauge to vertical or
            horizontal.

            Accepted values as defined in <@{"gadgets/fuelgauge.h" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File"}> are:

               @{"FGORIENT_HORIZ" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 73}
               @{"FGORIENT_VERT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 74}

            Defaults to @{"FGORIENT_HORIZ" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 73}

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Percent" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 39} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Enable/Disable Percentage display.
            Percentage is displayed in the center of the gauge using
            the requested font, provided it fits within the gadget bounds.

            Defaults to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Ticks" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 42} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
            Sets the number of "tickmarks" rendered along the bottom
            of the gadget. Take note, the tickmarks are rendered within
            the gadgets size dimentions. Values greater than 0 enable
            the tick mark(s).

            Defaults to 0

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_ShortTicks" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 45} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
            Enables rendering of "shortticks", smaller size tickmarks
            rendered in between the larger tick marks.

            Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98},

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_TickSize" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 48} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Sets the size, in pixels, of the large tickmarks.
            Shorttick size is TickHeight / 2. Note, if @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500} setting
            @{"FUELGAUGE_Ticks" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 42} non-zero, then you may need to 0 this as
            well depending on the fuelgauge release version!

            Defaults to 5 pixels

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_TickPen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 51} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Pen number used to render the tickmarks.

            Defaults to @{"SHINEPEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 97}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_PercentPen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 54} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Pen number used to render the percentage text label.

            Defaults to @{"TEXTPEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 96}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_EmptyPen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 60} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Pen number used to render the empty section of the gauge.

            Defaults to @{"BACKGROUNDPEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_FillPen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 57} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Pen number used to render the filled section of the gauge.

            Defaults to @{"BACKGROUNDPEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_VarArgs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 63} (@{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49})
            Varargs data array to supply data for @{"RawDoFmt()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/exec/RawDoFmt"} when
            format specifiers are to be used in @{"GA_Text" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 62} text strings.
            The VarArgs internal result buffer is 128 bytes, take care
            not to exceed this buffer.

            Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

        @{"FUELGAUGE_Justification" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 66} (@{"WORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 54})
            Justification mode of fuelgauge (@{"GA_Text" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 62}) text label.
            Percentage rendering, when enabled, is always centered.

            Supports:

                @{"FGJ_LEFT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 78}
                @{"FGJ_CENTER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 79}

            Defaults to @{"FGJ_LEFT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/fuelgauge.h/File" 78}.

            Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

